{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01UEbdv2B3daoK9TXD3fwdjK","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary Report: Run Grouping Headers Display Locations\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the codebase and found **all the locations** where run grouping headers are displayed with task IDs. The system currently shows only `{task.id}` and needs to be updated to show `{task.id}: {task.title}`.\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n#### 1. **Data Model - Task Information Available**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` (lines 22-28)\n  - `Task` struct has both `ID` and `Title` fields\n  \n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 74-83)\n  - `TaskEntry` struct has both `ID` and `Title` fields\n  - This is the primary data type used for task information in the web API\n\n#### 2. **Task Group Header Display - Backend Struct**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 519-526)\n  - `apiGroupedEntry` struct is used for the JSON API response\n  - Currently has: `TaskHeader`, `TaskID`, `TaskStatus`\n  - **Missing**: `TaskTitle` field (needs to be added here)\n\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 538-626)\n  - `groupAndSortRuns()` function builds the grouped entries\n  - Line 594 creates task header: `result = append(result, apiGroupedEntry{TaskHeader: true, TaskID: tid, TaskStatus: taskAggregateStatus(taskGroups[tid])})`\n  - This is where `TaskTitle` needs to be populated\n\n#### 3. **Task Group Header Display - HTML Template**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 34-36)\n  - Static template rendering for server-side HTML:\n    ```\n    {{if .TaskHeader}}\n    <tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: {{.TaskID}} <span class=\"badge badge-{{.TaskStatus}}\">{{.TaskStatus}}</span></td></tr>\n    ```\n  - **Current display**: `Task: {.TaskID}`\n  - **Needs to change to**: `Task: {.TaskID}: {.TaskTitle}`\n\n#### 4. **Task Group Header Display - JavaScript/Client-Side**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 115-118)\n  - JavaScript that dynamically polls the API and updates the table:\n    ```javascript\n    if (entry.task_header) {\n        var ts = entry.task_status || 'pending';\n        html += '<tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: ' + escapeHtml(entry.task_id) + ' <span class=\"badge badge-' + ts + '\">' + ts + '</span></td></tr>';\n        continue;\n    ```\n  - **Current display**: `Task: {entry.task_id}`\n  - **Needs to change to**: `Task: {entry.task_id}: {entry.task_title}`\n\n#### 5. **Task Information Provider**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 954-981)\n  - `GetLoopTasks()` method retrieves task information including `Title`\n  - Shows the complete data flow: Tasks have titles available from the orchestration loop\n\n#### 6. **API Response Handler**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1569-1589)\n  - `handleAPITasks()` endpoint returns TaskEntry objects with titles\n  - This confirms task titles are available in the API layer\n\n### Required Changes Summary:\n\n| Location | Type | Current | Change Needed |\n|----------|------|---------|---|\n| `handler.go:519-526` | Struct | `TaskID`, `TaskStatus` | Add `TaskTitle` field |\n| `handler.go:594` | Code | Creates `apiGroupedEntry{TaskHeader: true, TaskID: tid, TaskStatus: ...}` | Add `TaskTitle: <lookup>` |\n| `runs.html:34-36` | Template | `Task: {{.TaskID}}` | `Task: {{.TaskID}}: {{.TaskTitle}}` |\n| `runs.html:115-118` | JS | `Task: ' + entry.task_id` | `Task: ' + entry.task_id + ': ' + entry.task_title` |\n\n### Architecture Context:\n- The `groupAndSortRuns()` function receives `[]*domain.Run` objects which have `TaskID` field\n- Task titles are available via `taskProvider.GetLoopTasks()` which returns `[]TaskEntry` with full title information\n- The grouping logic needs to be enhanced to look up and attach task titles to the header entries\n\nAll absolute file paths:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a45b007c42505258b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61076\ntool_uses: 36\nduration_ms: 48216</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e3f34296-02df-46c1-8f5c-4634c003d0b4","uuid":"443958fe-da3a-4df7-8085-7af81a73303b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to find where run grouping headers are displayed in this Go project. The current behavior shows \"{task.id}\" and needs to show \"{task.id}: {task.title}\". \n\nSearch for:\n1. Any code related to \"group\" headers in the context of runs\n2. Any code that formats or displays task IDs in headers\n3. Look for task-related types that have id and title fields\n4. Search for \"grouping\" or \"group\" in the codebase\n5. Look at the CLI status/display code\n\nBe very thorough - check all display/formatting code, CLI output code, and any templates.","agentId":"a45b007c42505258b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information I need. Let me create a comprehensive summary document:\n\n## Summary Report: Run Grouping Headers Display Locations\n\nI've conducted a thorough search of the codebase and found **all the locations** where run grouping headers are displayed with task IDs. The system currently shows only `{task.id}` and needs to be updated to show `{task.id}: {task.title}`.\n\n### Key Findings:\n\n#### 1. **Data Model - Task Information Available**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/host/task.go` (lines 22-28)\n  - `Task` struct has both `ID` and `Title` fields\n  \n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 74-83)\n  - `TaskEntry` struct has both `ID` and `Title` fields\n  - This is the primary data type used for task information in the web API\n\n#### 2. **Task Group Header Display - Backend Struct**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 519-526)\n  - `apiGroupedEntry` struct is used for the JSON API response\n  - Currently has: `TaskHeader`, `TaskID`, `TaskStatus`\n  - **Missing**: `TaskTitle` field (needs to be added here)\n\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 538-626)\n  - `groupAndSortRuns()` function builds the grouped entries\n  - Line 594 creates task header: `result = append(result, apiGroupedEntry{TaskHeader: true, TaskID: tid, TaskStatus: taskAggregateStatus(taskGroups[tid])})`\n  - This is where `TaskTitle` needs to be populated\n\n#### 3. **Task Group Header Display - HTML Template**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 34-36)\n  - Static template rendering for server-side HTML:\n    ```\n    {{if .TaskHeader}}\n    <tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: {{.TaskID}} <span class=\"badge badge-{{.TaskStatus}}\">{{.TaskStatus}}</span></td></tr>\n    ```\n  - **Current display**: `Task: {.TaskID}`\n  - **Needs to change to**: `Task: {.TaskID}: {.TaskTitle}`\n\n#### 4. **Task Group Header Display - JavaScript/Client-Side**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (lines 115-118)\n  - JavaScript that dynamically polls the API and updates the table:\n    ```javascript\n    if (entry.task_header) {\n        var ts = entry.task_status || 'pending';\n        html += '<tr class=\"run-task-header\"><td colspan=\"9\">Task: ' + escapeHtml(entry.task_id) + ' <span class=\"badge badge-' + ts + '\">' + ts + '</span></td></tr>';\n        continue;\n    ```\n  - **Current display**: `Task: {entry.task_id}`\n  - **Needs to change to**: `Task: {entry.task_id}: {entry.task_title}`\n\n#### 5. **Task Information Provider**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` (lines 954-981)\n  - `GetLoopTasks()` method retrieves task information including `Title`\n  - Shows the complete data flow: Tasks have titles available from the orchestration loop\n\n#### 6. **API Response Handler**\n- **File**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1569-1589)\n  - `handleAPITasks()` endpoint returns TaskEntry objects with titles\n  - This confirms task titles are available in the API layer\n\n### Required Changes Summary:\n\n| Location | Type | Current | Change Needed |\n|----------|------|---------|---|\n| `handler.go:519-526` | Struct | `TaskID`, `TaskStatus` | Add `TaskTitle` field |\n| `handler.go:594` | Code | Creates `apiGroupedEntry{TaskHeader: true, TaskID: tid, TaskStatus: ...}` | Add `TaskTitle: <lookup>` |\n| `runs.html:34-36` | Template | `Task: {{.TaskID}}` | `Task: {{.TaskID}}: {{.TaskTitle}}` |\n| `runs.html:115-118` | JS | `Task: ' + entry.task_id` | `Task: ' + entry.task_id + ': ' + entry.task_title` |\n\n### Architecture Context:\n- The `groupAndSortRuns()` function receives `[]*domain.Run` objects which have `TaskID` field\n- Task titles are available via `taskProvider.GetLoopTasks()` which returns `[]TaskEntry` with full title information\n- The grouping logic needs to be enhanced to look up and attach task titles to the header entries\n\nAll absolute file paths:\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`\n- `/workspace/internal/host/task.go`\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`"}],"totalDurationMs":48216,"totalTokens":61076,"totalToolUseCount":36,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":580,"cache_read_input_tokens":59230,"output_tokens":1266,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":580},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standar